wiki.content:
Started life as 'Imodium', a tribute to the gastrointestinal complains of Tad Doyle of [band]Tad[/band].  Cobain had watched him vomiting each morning on their UK tour together and offered to help him by holding the bin for him in which to vomit into.  However, when Nirvana came to record the song, it had mutated into a complex narrative, with Cobain's parting "she said" suggesting a captured argument.
